          We recommend wearing comfortable clothing and sturdy, closed-toe
          shoes, such as sneakers or hiking boots. Since temperatures can drop
          at higher altitudes, bringing a jacket or windbreaker is advisable.
          Sunglasses are also useful to protect your eyes from the sun and wind.
          We’ll provide all the necessary flying equipment, including helmets
          and harnesses.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Accordion Item 5 -->
    <div id="accordion-button-5" class="border rounded-xl border-slate-200 hover:cursor-pointer px-3 py-4 transition-all">
      <div
        class="w-full flex justify-between items-center"
      >
        <span id="header-5" class="font-semibold text-neutral-500">
          What happens if the weather conditions aren’t ideal on the day of my
          flight?
        </span>
        <span
          id="icon-5"
          class="transition-transform duration-300"
        >
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            viewBox="0 0 16 16"
            fill="currentColor"
            class="w-4 h-4"
          >
            <path
              d="M8.75 3.75a.75.75 0 0 0-1.5 0v3.5h-3.5a.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5h3.5v3.5a.75.75 0 0 0 1.5 0v-3.5h3.5a.75.75 0 0 0 0-1.5h-3.5v-3.5Z"
